snippet.textDisplay:
This song is a rare phenomena which collaborates all kind of voices around the country for celebrating Womanhood. I never heard a song which is near to the comprehensive skills of reflecting the emotions in the lyrics. The lyrics are pooled together from Scattered portions in the CS terrain. Haniya & Rachel's tappy and bold voices handover the emotions of the song to Shamu Bai a lady with the mystic voice from the Outskirts , when she starts singing a Bhajan like "Kabira.." the whole mood of the song goes from "Strength of Womanhood" to the "Compassion of Womanhood", Song ends up with Ariana & Amrina's Humming portions - which is also from the coldest outskirts , From the "Compassion" to "Motivation" as they say only one word through out the song which is "Pareek" ! Which means "Lets Go"

Absolutely wonderful treat for ears !
